                      <div align="center">
                        <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
                          <tr>
                            <td width="100%" bgcolor="#004242">
                              <p align="center" style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 150%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma" color="#FFFFFF">DESCRIPTION</font></b></td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr><td width="100%">
                              <p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td width="100%">
                              <p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">
This expanse of sea known as the Ocean of Tears is full of many creatures to tackle and quests to fulfill. Most players simply know it as the zone between Freeport and Butcherblock Mountains, but the Ocean of Tears is far from just a boat ride.  I have broken the Ocean down into the known islands.
<br><br>
<b>Zachariah Reigh Island (Loc -2000, 7500)</b><br>
This is the boats first stop when heading to Freeport from Butcherblock.  Nothing much to this island except for three houses and a few NPCs.  Inside the western most house, you will find a vendor that sells food, water and buys anything you have to sell.  The only other site on the island is an Orc Spire like those found in other zones though no Orcs reside here.
<br><br>
<b>Twin Tines (Loc -1200, +2000)</b><br>
Four Aqua Goblins and two Sirens reside here, all around level 10.
<br><br>
<b>Allizewsaur Island (Loc -3300, -500)</b><br>
A few Island Goblins of very low level inhabit this island.  It is also the home of Allizewsaur, the large Dinosaur-like creature that kills everyone on sight.  Allizawsaur spawns and can be commonly found here, but it also often travels around the Ocean of Tears.
<br><br>
<b>Grey Isle (Loc -800, -6700)</b><br>
Ever wonder what very high level PC's are doing in this zone?  Well, more likely than not they are at the Grey Isle as a trio of Spectres reside here.  They stand or float next to a spire on top of the island and are in the upper 30s.  The island's other inhabitants are gargoyles ranging in level from 19-22.  Good hunting on the gargoyles, but be sure to keep some distance from the Spectres.
<br><br>
<b>Oracle of K'arnon (Loc -600, -8200)</b><br>
This island is overrun with Island Goblins ranging in levels from the Shamans (16) to the Warriors (low to mid 20s).  The Oracle Island isn't that good for solo play, but a good group would do well.  Other occupants of note are the Oracle of K'Arnon (level 35) and his protector (level 40).  The main tactic employed against them is to levitate the whole party and then cast from off shore where the guard cannot reach you.  This tactic has been successfully used by much lower level characters then the Oracle.  Another common tactic is to have a tank pull the Paladin (the Oracle's protector) and run away SoW'd.  That leaves the rest of the party with the Oracle, an easier battle.  Once the Oracle is dead, your tank can either zone or bring the Paladin back to the island.
<br><br>
<b>Pirate Isle (Loc +1600, -6200)</b><br>
This island holds the pirate clan on the northeast point of the island.  Beware that even if considered green, all will come if one is attacked.  They range in level from 16 to low 20s.  The Captain sometimes carries the Bracer of Erollisi.  Gornit occupies the shore near the pirate camp and Seafury Cyclops roam the hills.
<br><br>
<b>Mudtoe Island (Loc +1300, -7900)</b><br>
The easiest way to get to this island is to get off the boat at its first stop after leaving Freeport to Butcherblock.  Then head to your left and swim to Mudtoe Island.  Once you get to Mudtoe, you will see a small ruined keep.  This tower is the dwelling place of a High Elven that sells a few different spells.  The Mudtoe Brothers also reside on this island and are part of a dwarven quest.  A Cyclops also roams the island and the popular Ancient Cyclops spawns here every now and then.  To make him spawn, simply kill the single Cyclops spawn until the AC pops.  Note that the Cyclops has a few placeholders as well, all lower level.
<br><br>
<b>Sisterhood Isle (Loc +1200, -9400)</b><br>
This is the first boat stop when leaving Freeport to Butcherblock.  On the southern edge of the island, you will find a tent and a Dwarven vendor.  The sisters of Erollisi roam the hills.  Both the sisters and the variety of other NPCs found here are popular targets for evil races.
<br><br>
<b>Aviak Island (Loc +1100, 3300)</b><br>
Another good hunting spot for mid level characters.  The Aviaks here are indifferent to you and don't KOS.  In addition, there is no faction adjustment for killing them.  Simply pull them to shore and kill.  The Aviaks range in level from low teens to low 20s.  A named Aviak, Gull Skytalon, spawns infrequently and is level 25.  He drops Fine Steel weapons.
<br><br>
The Ocean of Tears is a great place to hunt and loot for a character in the low teens all the way to level 50 and should not be overlooked.
                           </font></td>
                          </tr>
